'''Walili''' (s [[Tifinaɣ|tfinaɣ]]: ''ⵡⴰⵍⵉⵍⵉ''; s [[Tutlayt Taɛṛabt|Tɛṛabt]]: ''وليلي''; s [[Tutlayt Talatiniyt|Tlatiniyt]] d tutlayin yaḍnin n Uṛubba: ''Volubilis'') tga yat tmdint tamaziɣt taqdimt, tettuṣka ɣ tasut tiss kṛaḍt nɣ d tiss kkuẓt dat n tlalit, tga yadlli tamaẓunt n [[Muriṭanya|tgldit n Muriṭanya]]. Tga ɣilad yan [[Adɣar adrzan|udɣar adrzan]] illa ɣ [[Azaɣar n Says|uzaɣar n Says]] iḍfṛn i [[Walili (Tagrawt)|tgrawt n wakal n Walili]] ɣ [[Tasga n Mknas|tsga n Mknas]].
<ref name="unesco">[https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/836 Archaeological Site of Volubilis, [[Yunisku]]]</ref> Ɣ tasut tiss 8 issnta gis [[Idris Ibn Ɛabdullah]] anbaḍ n [[Al Adarisa]] ɣ [[Lmɣrib]], ɣ tasut tiss 11 fln tt imzdaɣ lliɣ immutty unbaḍ n Al Adarisa s tmdint n [[Fas]], tugtt nnsn mmuttin s tmdint n [[Mulay Dris Ẓṛhun]]. Ssntan gis irzzutn irkyulujitn zɣ tizwiri n tasut tiss 20, aylli gis ittyafan yujja tt ad tettuzmim ɣ tlgamt n idɣarn imaḍlann n [[Yunisku]] asggʷas 1997.<ref name="unesco"/>

== Ism ==
[[Afaylu:Volubilis_-_Vue_générale.jpg|gauche|vignette|220x220px|Tawlaft n ixrban n Walili]]
Tugtt n imrza urmn ad ssfrun ism n Walili zɣ tguri talatinit [wulibulis], nɣ zɣ iɣbula aɛṛabn, zund [[Carl Juzif Tiṣu]] ([[:fr:Charles-Joseph Tissot|fr]]) (1828–1884) lli innan mas tettubdar '''Walili''' ɣ kra n iɣbula n [[Taɛṛabt]] s yism '''''Qaṣṛ Farɛun'''''  (قصر فرعون ''Iɣrm n frɛun'')<ref name="zamane"/>, ttun nɣ d ur rin ad rzun s unamk ɣ tdlsa d tutlayt n imzdaɣ inṣliyn n udɣar, aylli yujjan aẓuṛ n yism ur ittyawssan s tnɣda, macc irwas is ar itturray s tguri [[Tamaziɣt]] [[Walilt]] nna igan yan imɣi ar ittmɣay ɣ tamwin n Walili.<ref name="african">[https://web.archive.org/web/20131020180151/http://www.awhf.net/?p=573 African World Heritage Fund, ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITE OF VOLUBILIS]</ref> Mklli iẓḍaṛ yism n Walili ad dars tili tzdayt ula d yism n yat tqbilt tamaziɣt bdrn tt imrza n [[Amzruy|umzruy]] [[Iṛumiyn|iṛumiyn]] s yism [[Ulubilitani]].<ref name="zamane">[https://web.archive.org/web/20200610200648/https://zamane.ma/ar/%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A3%D9%88-%D9%82%D8%B5%D8%B1-%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%B9%D9%88%D9%86-2  مجلة زمان، وليلي أو قصر فرعون]</ref>

== Adɣar ==<!-- ad ur tsnflm aḍṛiṣ ad ati druɣ srs ɣ yat tsmɣurt, tanmmirt -->
Tettuṣka tmdint n '''Walili''' ɣ uɣlla n [[Adrar n Ẓṛhun|udrar n Ẓṛhun]] tama [[Asif n Xuman|wasif n Xuman]] d [[Asif n Fṛṭaṣa|wasif n Fṛṭaṣa]], tlkm tjumma nns 42 hiktar, taggug s 3 kilumitr f tmdint n [[Mulay Dris Ẓṛhun]], 30 kilumitr f tmdint n [[Mknas]], d 63 kilumitr f tmdint n [[Fas]]. llan tama nns kra n izaɣarn mu ifulki wakal nnsn, ar smɣayn anawn n waddagn, s lawan akkʷ addagn n uzmmur nna igan llsas n tdmsa ɣ tsga.<ref name="african"/>

== Amzruy ==<!-- ad ur tsnflm aḍṛiṣ ad ati druɣ srs ɣ yat tsmɣurt, tanmmirt -->
Ikka tt nn udɣar issutln i '''Walili''' ittuzdaɣ zɣ uzmz Atlanti ([[:en:Atlantic (period)|en]]) d unyuliti ([[:en:Neolithic|en]]), attay n 5.000 n isggʷasn aya. Irzzutn irkyulujitn ttuskarnin ɣ udɣar n ''Walili'' sduggan d kra idqqi mi itturray usakud ar azmz anyuliti, irwas kra n igzman ttyafanin ɣ [[Ibirya]].<ref name="Carrasco">Carrasco, J. L. Escacena (2000). "Archaeological relationship between North Africa and Iberia". In Arnaiz-Villena, Antonio; Martínez-Laso, Jorge; Gómez-Casado, Eduardo (eds.). Prehistoric Iberia: Genetics, Anthropology, and Linguistics. New York: Springer. ISBN 0-306-46364-4.</ref> Kkan tt nn gis [[Iqarṭajiyn]] ɣ tasut tis 8, aya mlant t kra n tmitar lli ɣinn fln, zun d ixrban n lmaɛbad n wakuc Baɛl, idqqi nnsn d kra n iẓṛan ɣ gzin tirra nnsn s [[Tutlayt Tafiniqiyt]].<ref name="Rogerson">Rogerson, Barnaby (2010). Marrakesh, Fez and Rabat. London: Cadogan Guides. ISBN 978-1-86011-432-8.</ref> 

Tkcim tmdint n Walili ɣ [[Muriṭanya|Tgldit n Muritanya]] ddu tnbaḍt n [[Iṛumiyn]] ḍffiṛ taḍuṛi n [[Qaṛṭaj]] ɣ usggʷas 146 dat ntlalit.<ref name="Rogerson"/> Tsul tzrirt n [[Ifiniqiyn]] ɣ Walili mnnaw isggʷsn f alliɣ yad tlla ddu ifasn n [[Iṛumiyn]], ɣ imdyatn n tzrirt ad, llan inzzurfa lli dar iɣama yism aqaṛṭajiy [[Suffit]].<ref name="Parker">Parker, Philip (2010). The Empire Stops Here: A Journey along the Frontiers of the Roman World. London: Random House. ISBN 978-0-224-07788-0.</ref> Issnta [[Yuba II]] tuṣka n yat tamaẓunt tagldant ɣ Walili daṛat n mad t issnṣb [[Ugustin]] f udabu n [[Muriṭanya|Tgldit n Muritanya]] ɣ useggwas 25 dat n tlalit.<ref name="Davies">Davies, Ethel (2009). North Africa: The Roman Coast. Chalfont St Peter, Bucks: Bradt Travel Guides. ISBN 978-1-84162-287-3.</ref> Iɣra [[Yuba Wiss Sin]] ɣ [[Ṛuma]], itahl s [[Klyubaṭṛa Silini II]], illis n [[Maṛk Anṭuni]] and [[Cleopatra]], mqqar iga Yuba d yiwis [[Bṭulimi]] imaziɣn s laṣl, tiɣri d uswingm nnsn gan iṛumiyn, slawann akkʷ [[Taẓuṛi]] d [[Tamsdagt|Tmsdagt]] taṛumiyt taqburt, zun d tmamkt lli s iṣka Yuba tamdint n Wlili.<ref name="Rogerson"/>
